{
  "texts": [
    "We denote by i the image/bag index, by j the instance/patch index within image x i, and by k the class/label index.",
    "Let x i be the input image and x j i its j-th instance.",
    "Instance-level predictions are first made independently, and then aggregated to produce the final image-level prediction.Instead of uniform sampling, we introduce an instance sampler to extract meaningful sub-regions from ANA images.",
    "Let t j i denote a 0-1 label vector, where the k th element t j i,k is equal to 1 if l k is present in x j i, and 0 otherwise.",
    "The general idea is to find a vector α j i = {α j i,k } for each instance x j i, where the k th element α j i,k indicates how confident the learner is about the presence of l k in the instance."
  ]
}